The RCR Stability Theorem Paper
RCR Stability Theorem: Mathematical Validation of Coherence
Status: v1.0
Domain: Control Systems / Sovereign OS Kernel
Author: Architect
This document presents the formal mathematical proof that the Reciprocal Conservation of Resources (RCR) Principle, when enforced by the Sovereign OS closure dynamics, guarantees asymptotic stability of the residual process and realizes the Coherence Goal State R˙→0\dot R \to 0R˙→0.

The OS is the operational demo; this theorem is the formal proof.


1. Core Definitions and Variables
We work with dimensionless conserved momentum PPP, a normalized unit that can represent energy, trust, or information flow.
