2. Assumptions (RCR Axioms)
Axiom 1 — Residual Dynamics.
The residual evolves as
R˙(t)=−k C(t)+d(t),k>0,\dot R(t)=-k\,C(t)+d(t),\qquad k>0,R˙(t)=−kC(t)+d(t),k>0,
where d(t)d(t)d(t) collects exogenous leak and input variation (note that since R=I−CR=I-CR=I−C, the term I˙\dot II˙ is absorbed into ddd).
Axiom 2 — RCR Closure Policy.
C(t)=α I(t)+β R(t),α>0, β>0.C(t)=\alpha\,I(t)+\beta\,R(t),\qquad \alpha>0,\ \beta>0 .C(t)=αI(t)+βR(t),α>0, β>0.
Axiom 3 — Bounded Disturbance.
∣d(t)∣ ≤ ε I(t).|d(t)|\ \le\ \varepsilon\,I(t).∣d(t)∣ ≤ εI(t).
Axiom 4 — Injected Energy Floor.
I(t) ≥ Imin⁡ >0(and optionally I(t)≤Imax⁡<∞ if an upper bound is desired).I(t)\ \ge\ I_{\min}\ >0 \quad (\text{and optionally } I(t)\le I_{\max}<\infty\ \text{if an upper bound is desired}).I(t) ≥ Imin​ >0(and optionally I(t)≤Imax​<∞ if an upper bound is desired).

3. RCR Stability Theorem (ISS & Ultimate Boundedness)
Theorem. Under Axioms 1–4, with k,α,β>0k,\alpha,\beta>0k,α,β>0 and I(t)∈[Imin⁡,Imax⁡]I(t)\in[I_{\min},I_{\max}]I(t)∈[Imin​,Imax​], the residual system is input-to-state stable (ISS) with respect to d(t)d(t)d(t) and is uniformly ultimately bounded (UUB). In particular, if
kα > ε,k\alpha\ >\ \varepsilon,kα > ε,
then there exists a constant ultimate bound
 ∣R(t)∣ ≤ B(ε) := εkβ Imax⁡ for all sufficiently large t.\boxed{\ |R(t)|\ \le\ B(\varepsilon)\ :=\ \frac{\varepsilon}{k\beta}\,I_{\max}\ } \quad \text{for all sufficiently large } t . ∣R(t)∣ ≤ B(ε) := kβε​Imax​ ​for all sufficiently large t.
Corollary (Asymptotic Coherence).
If policy tightening drives ε→0\varepsilon\to 0ε→0 (perfect reciprocity), then B(ε)→0B(\varepsilon)\to 0B(ε)→0 and consequently
R(t)→0,R˙(t)→0as t→∞,R(t)\to 0,\qquad \dot R(t)\to 0\quad \text{as } t\to\infty,R(t)→0,R˙(t)→0as t→∞,
achieving the Coherence Goal State.

Remark (Sufficiency vs. Necessity).
The margin kα>εk\alpha>\varepsilonkα>ε is a sufficient dissipativity condition for a clean linear term; stability is also aided by the intrinsic quadratic damping −kβR2-k\beta R^2−kβR2 with β>0\beta>0β>0.


