With I(t) ≥ Imin > 0 and kα > ε, the linear dissipation term is strictly positive, and the quadratic
term provides additional damping. Standard ISS/UUB arguments yield the stated bound; with an
explicit upper bound Imax, one conservative choice is
B(ε) = ε
kβ Imax.
If ε = 0, then V˙ ≤ −kα|R|I − kβR2 and R(t) → 0 globally.
5 Interpretation for Sovereign OS
Ultimate Boundedness. The residual ethical debt R(t) cannot diverge; it is forced into an ε-scaled
neighborhood set by B(ε).
Operational Mandate. The Audit & Integrity Console must ensure kα > ε and track Imin, Imax
to maintain the dissipativity margin.
